`crates/ctx-cage/src` is the whole `ctx-cage` crate: it builds and runs an offline, bind-mounted sandbox (`bwrap`) around an agent process, brokers the only network egress through a host-side proxy, and drives one run's lifecycle (prepare → run → teardown) so a caller gets a single `execute()` entry point with guaranteed cleanup and an unaltered exit code. Depending on this crate gets you `lifecycle::execute`, the `bwrap`-arg builder, and the `proxy` request-rewrite logic — nothing else in the workspace should construct bwrap flags or read/write the API key directly.

The subtree is organized around a few load-bearing constants and conventions that every child must agree on: the cage-side path constants from `bwrap::config` are the only strings anything binds targets to (lifecycle, `/opt/cage/rules.md`, and `bwrap::build` all reference them); `target_root` is canonicalized exactly once in `lifecycle::execute` per ADR-046, and no downstream phase (bwrap build, `runtime.rs`'s trust-map key, `env.rs`'s binds) may re-derive or bypass that; and the real API key or OAuth credential never enters the cage — it's injected only by `proxy.rs` on the host side, reached via the UNIX socket bind-mounted at `/run/ctx/api.sock`, with `runtime.rs` and `lifecycle/env.rs` both independently upholding "no secret crosses into the sandbox." `cli.rs` and `bin/` share the billed-mode gating pattern (`--allow-spend`/env var) but resolve it independently per binary — `ctx-cage` requires explicit opt-in, `ctx-run` treats invocation itself as authorization.

`error.rs` supplies the crate-wide `CageError` (Io/Json/Protocol) used consistently across `runtime.rs`, `proxy.rs`, and `lifecycle`; no module hand-rolls its own top-level error type. `lib.rs` is pure doc-and-re-export plus two `include_str!`-embedded assets (cage rules, resolv.conf stub) whose presence is enforced at compile time, not runtime. A typical cross-cutting change (new bind path, new env var, new mount) touches `bwrap/config.rs`, `lifecycle/env.rs`, and `lifecycle/prepare.rs` together.

No intent.md exists for this directory or several subdirectories (`bin/`, `proxy/`) to check divergence against.